                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13837/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dodge reports that the consul at Tegucigalpa informs him that Bailey and the
                        <hi rend="italic">Goldsboro</hi> are held at Ceiba and that it is advisable
                    that an officer come as soon as possible to take him into custody. The consul
                    wishes to know when the officer will arrive, Mr. Dodge states that the
                    Government of Honduras only requires a copy of the indictment issued by the New
                    York authorities.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
